FBIS3-60819 "jptot001__l94067" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Deputy Minister Rejects Hamas Cease-Fire Conditions Deputy Defense Minister Rejects Hamas Terms TA2412205893 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 24 Dec 93 TA2412205893 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Deputy Defense Minister Mordekhay Gur said tonight that Hamas is succeeding in carrying out painful attacks, but is not in control in the territories. He said that Israel rejects the conditions presented by Hamas for a cease-fire, and regards them as a provocation. Hamas leaders want to present themselves as negotiating with Israel, but we chose to negotiate with the PLO because it is the main force in the Palestinian street, Gur said. [passage omitted on politicians' comments]
